Concerned about the decadence in the Nigerian society, the Anglican Bishop of Lagos West, Rt. Rev’d Olusola Odedeji, has called on all Nigerians to return to God if they genuinely want a better country. According to the bishop, the task of rebuilding the country should not be left to the politicians alone.  In his message to the nation at the beginning of the New Year, Bishop Odedeji called on all citizens to seek the face of God on behalf of the country in the year. He said “insecurity is rife all over the country, the common people have nothing to eat and unemployment is the order of the day. There must be a change at this point, but the citizens cannot afford to go to bed in between elections.”   Declare for the presidency in 2023, group tells Tinubu     Sanwo-Olu intervenes in Magodo estate crisis     INEC releases timetable for Ekiti governorship poll   While quoting Matthew 2 of the Bible, the Bishop said God who, through the shining star revealed Jesus Christ to the wise men, is ever ready to guide those who trust in him. According to him, “divine guidance is all about God being the only one who can lead successfully”. He stated further that even though mighty men and women abound in the world, there’s only one Almighty in the universe. - Advertisement - He reasoned that divine guidance doesn’t foreclose tribulations and difficulties or challenges in life, but one is assured of victory when the siege is over. He also said divine guidance operates through His words, through His spirit, through His servants, through dreams, and through sermons, Christian movies and literature, these are still available today, he counselled.